{
  "text": "For the validation experiments reported below, we begin with a simple power model configuration that can be verified by measurements of the WRT54GL target device using an external power meter. The model is implemented as a daemon on the test device. In our model configuration, we assume that the total power consumption of the device is the sum of the consumption of the components. We begin by adding two components to the model, the ports and the chassis as shown in Table I . This model specifies a fixed cost for the idle state of each component. We also specify a fixed cost for the \"full load\" state of ports (i.e., one in which there is no proportionality of power consumption with load). Our rational for this configuration is due to observations in prior work that the power profile of contemporary switches is not very sensitive to the amount of traffic they are forwarding [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
